ACTIVE THREADS
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1. THE HUNGER CLOCK
   Aritomo Nakadai (Renraku OS, 3rd retirement) is dying. His soul is in escrow.
   Someone is rewriting the withdrawal terms.
   [STATUS: DORMANT] – No leads yet.

2. IDOL OF RUST [RESOLVED – SESSION 1]
   The container weeps. Hana Sato, age 7, drowned 2041, has been waiting forty years.
   Yuki Tanaka opened the door. She went to Lake Tazawa to complete Emiko's pilgrimage.
   [RESOLUTION: Container identified as kankobito vessel. Cult identified as waiters.
    Leader unknown. Woman in video = Yuki Tanaka, now missing.]

3. THE WAGES OF MERCY
   A Redmond free clinic is three months behind on Knight Errant "protection" fees.
   The alternative is eviction. The alternative to eviction is cremation.
   [STATUS: ACTIVE] – Epirus is there. 3 days until next payment.

4. YUKI'S PILGRIMAGE
   Yuki Tanaka, terminated Mitsuhama analyst, debtor, Mira's sister.
   She found Emiko Sato's research. She paid off her mother's 40-year debt.
   She opened the container. She went to Lake Tazawa to finish what Emiko started.
   She has not returned.
   [STATUS: ACTIVE] – Key obtained. Location known. Next: Iwate Prefecture.

5. THE EIGHT
   Eight Mitsuhama employees, all with debt, all with archive access, all terminated.
   Two dead. Two missing. Two relocated. One institutionalized.
   One: Nakamura, Division Manager, no debt, still employed.
   Yuki was the eighth.
   [STATUS: ACTIVE] – Pattern recognized. Nexus: Nakamura.

